  "prompt": "How many grafts are needed to get a full beard by facial hair transplant? How much will it cost in India?",
  "response": "The number of grafts required for a full beard transplant can vary significantly depending on several factors, including the density of the existing beard, the desired fullness, and the area to be covered. On average, a full beard transplant might require anywhere from 2,000 to 3,000 grafts. Here's a rough breakdown:\n\n- **Mustache and Goatee**: Around 500 to 1,000 grafts\n- **Cheeks**: Around 1,000 to 1,500 grafts per side\n- **Sideburns and Jawline**: Additional 500 to 1,000 grafts\n\nThe cost of a beard transplant in India can also vary based on the location of the clinic, the experience of the surgeon, the technique used (FUE or FUT), and the number of grafts required. On average, the cost can range from INR 30 to INR 100 per graft. Therefore, for a full beard transplant:\n\n- **2,000 grafts**: INR 60,000 to INR 200,000\n- **3,000 grafts**: INR 90,000 to INR 300,000\n\nIt's important to consult with a qualified surgeon to get a personalized estimate based on your specific needs and goals. They can provide a more accurate assessment of the number of grafts required and the total cost.",
